intro: Swainsona extrajacens, commonly known as the golden wattle, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It is a shrub or small tree that can grow up to 5 meters in height, characterized by its bright yellow flowers that bloom in spring. The plant has compound leaves composed of several oval-shaped leaflets, and its flowers are clustered in racemes. Swainsona extrajacens is known for its ability to thrive in various soil types and is often found in coastal and inland areas. It plays an important role in local ecosystems and is a symbol of Australian biodiversity.
